AIM – OBJECTIVES
The main aim of the MSc Program “Microsystems and Nanodevices” (MINA) is to provide
a comprehensive and interdisciplinary education on the physics and chemistry of advanced nanomaterials, low-dimensional systems, quantum materials, as well as a robust training on pertinent technological applications which include, among other, electronic nanodevices, sensors, nanostructured materials for solar cells or catalysis, laser printing, nano-fluidic systems, etc.
